[SN]TITLE[SN]
Jack Baldwin: Peterborough United defender out for up to eight weeks

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Peterborough defender Jack Baldwin will have surgery on a knee injury and be out for up to eight weeks.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Baldwin has made 19 appearances for the League One side in all competitions this season.
The 23-year-old ruptured a ligament in the same knee in November 2014, making his return more than 12 months later.
Peterborough, who are sixth in the League One table, drew 2-2 with League Two side Notts County in the FA Cup second round on Sunday.
